    <p>A cue ball (white) hits another billiards ball (red). The red ball is initially at rest. The white ball's motion is at a 90&#176; angle to the motion of the red ball after the collision. After the collision, the ratio of speed of the white ball to that of the red ball is \(1:\sqrt 3\). What is the ratio of the initial speed to the final speed of the white ball? All balls have the same mass.</p>
    <br/>
    <multiplechoiceresponse direction="vertical" randomize="yes" type="MultipleChoice">
      <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
        <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">
              <text>\(1:\sqrt 3\)</text>
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">
              <text>\(1:2\)</text>
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="true">
              <text>\(2:1\)</text>
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">
              <text>\(\sqrt 3:1\)</text>
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">
              <text>\(1:1\)</text>
        </choice>
        <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">
              <text>\(1+\sqrt 3:\sqrt 3\)</text>
        </choice>
      </choicegroup>
    </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </problem>
